			<translation>There are no books, which I would prefer not to lack than these, and they must be truly understood by heart before al othersl. For public business,
				Marcantonio Gandino and Polyaenus, with Aristotele's 'Economics' and Cicero's 'On running for the consulship'. Mithridates' 'Pragmatic letter and speech against Rome'. The eulogies of 
				Frederick Feltrius, Ludovico Sforza, and Cesare Borgia, with the history of Catherine de' Medici. Bodin's 'Method for the easy knowledge of history' for all discourses.</translation>
